               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450512-name-906" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450512-name-906" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450512-name-906" type="surname" value="WATSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450512-name-906" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES WATSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a sergeant of the City-police, and live in Green Arbour-court, Moorfields. On the 14th of May I was in Green wick fair, in plain clothes—I heard a scuffle behind me, and on turning round observed my cigar-case in the bands of a man in plain clothes, who after<lb></lb>wards turned out to be an officer.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450512-name-907" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450512-name-907" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450512-name-907" type="surname" value="RAPSEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450512-name-907" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES RAPSEY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable R</hi> 102.) I was at Greenwich on the 14th of May, about four o'clock—I saw the prisoner and another go towards Watson, lift the tail of his coat, draw the cigar-case from bis pocket, and pass it to the other, who I immediately laid hold oft and took it from him—Watson turned round, and seeing the case in my hand, res<lb></lb>cued the prisoner, and took the cigar-case from me, thinking I bad taken it.</p>
               <p>
